# day3-data-modeling

## 1. Difference Between App, Object, Record, and Field

| Term | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| App | A collection of related tools, tabs, and objects designed for a business purpose | College Management App |
| Object | A database table that stores data | Student Object |
| Record | A single entry inside an object | Student: Rahul Kumar |
| Field | A column inside an object that stores specific information | Student Name, Roll Number |

---

## 2. Standard vs Custom Objects

| Standard Objects | Custom Objects |
|---|---|
| Pre-built by Salesforce | Created by users |
| Available by default | Built according to business needs |
| Examples: Account, Contact, Opportunity | Examples: Student, Course, Attendance |
| Cannot be deleted easily | Fully customizable |

### Standard Object Examples
- Account
- Contact
- Opportunity
- Lead

### Custom Object Examples
- Student
- Faculty
- Exam
- Attendance

