4. Formula Fields

Formula fields automatically calculate values using other field data.

Example 1: Student Age
TODAY() - Date_of_Birth__c

5. Validation Rules

Validation rules ensure correct data entry in Salesforce.

Example 1: Phone Number Validation
LEN(Phone__c) <> 10

This rule ensures the phone number contains exactly 10 digits.

Example 2: Prevent Negative Fee Amount
Fee_Amount__c < 0

This rule prevents users from entering negative fee values.

Example 3: Mandatory Email Validation
ISBLANK(Email__c)

6. Reflection: Why Structured Enterprise Data Matters

Structured enterprise data helps organizations store, manage, and analyze information efficiently. In Salesforce, properly organized data improves reporting, automation, security, and decision-making.

For a college management system, structured data helps track students, attendance, exams, fees, and faculty records accurately. It reduces errors, improves communication, and supports better administrative management.

Good data modeling also helps businesses scale applications easily and maintain consistency across departments.
